Here's a single, self-contained HTML file that accomplishes this. It uses a little bit of CSS for styling and JavaScript for the real-time logic and animation.

**Key Features:**

1.  **Real-time Reversal:** As you type, the output updates instantly.
2.  **Character-by-Character Animation:** When the reversed string changes, each character in the output fades in and slightly scales up, creating a pleasing "pop" effect.
3.  **Clean & Centered Layout:** Modern, minimalist design with everything centered.
4.  **Self-Contained:** All HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are within one file.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Real-time String Reverser</title>
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Mono:wght@300;400;700&display=swap');

        :root {
            --primary-color: #6200EE;
            --primary-light: #BB86FC;
            --primary-dark: #3700B3;
            --background-color: #121212;
            --surface-color: #1E1E1E;
            --on-background: #E0E0E0;
            --on-surface: #E0E0E0;
            --input-border: #424242;
            --input-focus-border: var(--primary-light);
            --animation-duration: 0.15s;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Roboto Mono', monospace;
            background-color: var(--background-color);
            color: var(--on-background);
            margin: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
            padding: 20px;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            overflow: hidden; /* Prevent scrollbar from animation */
        }

        .container {
            background-color: var(--surface-color);
            border-radius: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            padding: 40px;
            max-width: 600px;
            width: 100%;
            text-align: center;
            border: 1px solid var(--input-border);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary-light);
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            font-size: 2.2em;
            letter-spacing: -0.5px;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .input-group {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        #textInput {
            width: calc(100% - 40px);
            padding: 18px 20px;
            border: 2px solid var(--input-border);
            border-radius: 8px;
            background-color: var(--background-color);
            color: var(--on-surface);
            font-size: 1.1em;
            font-family: 'Roboto Mono', monospace;
            outline: none;
            transition: border-color 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: inset 0 1px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        #textInput::placeholder {
            color: #888;
        }

        #textInput:focus {
            border-color: var(--input-focus-border);
            box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(var(--primary-light-rgb), 0.3), inset 0 1px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        /* Define RGB values for primary-light for box-shadow rgba */
        :root {
            --primary-light-rgb: 187, 134, 252; /* Corresponds to #BB86FC */
        }

        .output-group {
            margin-top: 30px;
            min-height: 60px; /* Give some space even when empty */
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            flex-wrap: wrap; /* Allow characters to wrap */
            align-items: center;
        }

        #reversedOutput {
            font-size: 1.8em;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--primary-light);
            word-break: break-all; /* Ensure long words break */
            line-height: 1.4;
            display: flex; /* Use flex to allow individual character styling */
            justify-content: center;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .reversed-char {
            display: inline-block; /* Essential for transform/animation */
            opacity: 0;
            transform: scale(0.8);
            animation: fadeInScale var(--animation-duration) forwards ease-out;
            margin: 0 1px; /* Small spacing between characters */
            white-space: pre; /* Preserve spaces as individual characters */
        }

        /* Animation for individual characters */
        @keyframes fadeInScale {
            from {
                opacity: 0;
                transform: scale(0.8);
            }
            to {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: scale(1);
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>String Reverser</h1>

        <div class="input-group">
            <input type="text" id="textInput" placeholder="Type something here...">
        </div>

        <div class="output-group">
            <div id="reversedOutput"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        const textInput = document.getElementById('textInput');
        const reversedOutput = document.getElementById('reversedOutput');
        let previousReversedString = '';

        textInput.addEventListener('input', () => {
            const originalString = textInput.value;
            const reversedString = originalString.split('').reverse().join('');

            // Only update and animate if the string has actually changed
            if (reversedString !== previousReversedString) {
                updateReversedOutput(reversedString);
                previousReversedString = reversedString;
            }
        });

        function updateReversedOutput(newReversedString) {
            // Clear existing content
            reversedOutput.innerHTML = '';

            if (newReversedString.length === 0) {
                // Optionally display a placeholder if empty
                // reversedOutput.innerHTML = '<span style="color: #888; font-size: 0.8em;">Output will appear here</span>';
                return;
            }

            // Create a span for each character and append it
            for (let i = 0; i < newReversedString.length; i++) {
                const char = newReversedString[i];
                const charSpan = document.createElement('span');
                charSpan.className = 'reversed-char';
                charSpan.textContent = char;
                // Add a slight delay for a staggered animation effect
                charSpan.style.animationDelay = `${i * 0.03}s`; // Staggered delay
                reversedOutput.appendChild(charSpan);
            }
        }

        // Initial update in case there's pre-filled input (though not in this example)
        updateReversedOutput(textInput.value.split('').reverse().join(''));
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

