                <p>This is significantly better than <span class="notation">O(n²)</span>. If you double the input size, the number of operations roughly doubles, but with an additional logarithmic factor. For 100 items, it might be around 700 operations. For 1000 items, it's about 10,000 operations. This scales much more gracefully, making these algorithms suitable for large datasets.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
