                Imagine a system where a customer pays $15.00, but your system calculates their balance as $14.999999999999998. A check like <code>balance === 15.00</code> would fail, potentially leading to incorrect charges, unapplied payments, or other financial discrepancies.</li>
            <li><strong>Rounding Issues:</strong> While you can round floats for display, the underlying value is still inexact. If you perform calculations on already rounded numbers, or if the rounding isn't consistent, new errors can be introduced.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal and Auditing Ramifications:</strong> Inaccurate financial records are not just bad practice; they can have severe legal and auditing consequences.</li>
